    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "Born in Nairobi, Kenyan artist Wangechi Mutu gained widespread recognition and success in the art world soon after her graduation from the prestigious Yale School of Art. Her work often draws on her own experiences as a Black woman and a member of the African Diaspora and with her success, she has sought to aid other diasporic artists. With this goal in mind, Mutu founded Africa’s Out! to provide a platform for other African diasporic artists to advance their practice and shift Western perceptions of Africa, two major conceptual pillars throughout her oeuvre."
    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
